// Solution-style config: it owns no files itself, it only points at the two real projects.
//
// Therefore `tsc --noEmit` here CHECKS NOTHING. It does not follow references — it finds
// `"files": []`, has nothing to do, and exits 0. It looks exactly like a passing typecheck.
// That is not hypothetical: 11 errors and a silently dead feature (D25) accumulated behind
// a command that reported success every time.
//
// Use `npm run typecheck` (tsc -b). Build mode is what walks the references.
{
  "files": [],
  "references": [
    { "path": "./tsconfig.app.json" },
    { "path": "./tsconfig.node.json" }
  ]
}
